{"id":14881436,"mediaExerciseId":"ca008b54-de6e-4d39-9f6f-6e19ff46c345","exerciseName":"3","chapterName":"14","chapterTitle":"Cost of Capital","groupId":null,"groupTitle":null,"isPremium":true,"sectionName":"14.3","sectionTitle":"The Costs of Debt and Preferred Stock","pageNumber":465,"solutions":[{"id":5979836,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"$a)$ Because the coupon rate established the cost of debt whenever the debt was issued, it is a poor estimate when determining the cost of debt, that yield to maturity of the bond should be used to calculate a company's current cost of debt, a bond's yield-to-maturity indicates the current market price for debt issued within previous.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":181,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/82b73e4ca4350b7121540d43c5489189/ecbdc1ee3153515b028862333449f8d8/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":91,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/82b73e4ca4350b7121540d43c5489189/ecbdc1ee3153515b028862333449f8d8/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"$b)$ Any amount of interest payments a corporation must generate on recently borrowed funds to creditors is referred to as its cost of debt, the current market necessary return for outstanding bonds will become the company's cost of debt.\n\nThis yield-to-maturity seems to be the current market rate for identical debt securities, this cost of a company's debt is calculated by multiplying the yield to maturity rate by the market price of the bond.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":256,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/82b73e4ca4350b7121540d43c5489189/3f46c4ba8a697c77552279b8a1722be5/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":128,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/82b73e4ca4350b7121540d43c5489189/3f46c4ba8a697c77552279b8a1722be5/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"$c)$ There are two methods for calculating the cost for preferred stock:\n\nBy comparing the needed return on a similar stock to the constant dividend rate and the current market price of the preferred stock, precisely as with bonds.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":137,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/82b73e4ca4350b7121540d43c5489189/6d58b303e2ee73c7bcbfdfc1290f9bed/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":69,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/82b73e4ca4350b7121540d43c5489189/6d58b303e2ee73c7bcbfdfc1290f9bed/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"fadb1a5d-5f3d-45f5-bdb3-c63050394abd","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881437,"exerciseName":"1","page":472,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"a0f61353-6159-4b48-8ea9-bbbe5c1a1ed1","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-14-exercises-1-a0f61353-6159-4b48-8ea9-bbbe5c1a1ed1"},{"id":14881438,"exerci